Tales and legends form parts of the cultural wealth of a country. Who has not, on long winter nights with the light flickering and the wind howling in the trees, heard such stories. Who has not said to his/her mother just before going to sleep, ``Mummy, t
ell me a story"? And she had no sooner said ``Once upon a time there was ..." when we would close our eyes and hand ourselves over to the world of fairy stories and magic. A life without such magic would be all the poorer.
